{"label":"spawn","args":{"append_system_prompt":"To delegate self-contained subtasks, emit a <fork> tag with a YAML list of short task labels:\n<fork>\n- Write tests for auth module\n- Update API documentation\n</fork>\nEach task inherits your full conversation context and runs as an independent session. Multiple tasks run concurrently. Use fork when a subtask is self-contained — whether you're parallelizing independent work or delegating a task that benefits from full context inheritance. You'll receive the combined results in a <fork-results> message when all tasks complete.","extra_args":["--model","claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","--disallowed-tools","Task"],"prompt":"<fork-results>\n<task label=\"Create hello.txt with 'hello world' content\">\nDone! Created hello.txt with 'hello world' content.\n</task>\n<task label=\"Create goodbye.txt with 'goodbye world' content\">\nDone! Created goodbye.txt with 'goodbye world' content.\n</task>\n</fork-results>","resume":"6df0913d-150d-4ba4-a277-e8d97f84fe1b"},"result":{"Ok":null}}
